p: The first line reads neurological signs and symptoms all n = 50, the thrid column indicates Zika diagnosis by PCR or IgM (n = 26), and the fourth column shows Zika diagnosis by PCR or IgM and rash, joint pain, or conjunctivitis (n = 26), the sum is 52, no 50. In addition, if the individual data of the next line 10 + 16 +7 + 19 are added, it is equal to 52, so it should be reviewed why the total number of patients is exceeded by 2.
